deck: Golden Boy (ゴールデンボーイ Gōruden Bōi) is a Japanese manga series by Tatsuya Egawa about a 25-year-old freeter, pervert, and "travelling student" named Kintaro Oe (大江 錦太郎 Ōe Kintarō)
description: Kintaro, despite having met the requirements for a law degree, left Tokyo University without graduating. Golden Boy depicts his living the life of a free spirit, roaming Japan from town to town, job to job. During his travels, Kintaro meets several women whose lives he dramatically changes, despite poor first impressions. He constantly observes and studies the people and events around him, recording his findings in a notebook he carries on his belt.
name: Golden Boy

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ベルサイユのばら

Originally serialized in Margaret. This series is well-known for elevating shojo manga in general and being one of the first examples of manga to be used in Japan for educational purposes.

The first ten volumes of this series were the original collections, having been later reprinted in various forms numerous times over in later decades. The eleventh and twelfth volumes are additional material that was printed when the entire original collections were reprinted forty years after their first printing.
name: Berusaiyu No Bara
